<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Roman_Polanski&action=edit&section=25.php.html" title="Edit section: Writer">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Writer">Writer</span></h3>
<ul>
<li>Script for <i>A Taste for Women</i>,<a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0057827/fullcredits?ref_=tt_ov_wr#writers">[1]</a> [Scénario&#160;:<a href="http://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aimez-vous_les_femmes" class="extiw" title="fr:Aimez-vous les femmes">«Aimez-vous les femmes?»</a>] (1964)</li>
<li>Script for <i><a href="A_Day_at_the_Beach" title="A Day at the Beach">A Day at the Beach</a></i> (1970) based on the 1962 novel of the same name by <a href="Simon_Heere_Heeresma" title="Simon Heere Heeresma">Simon Heere Heeresma</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-RPinterviewsxvi_127-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-RPinterviewsxvi-127"><span>[</span>127<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>Polanski's autobiography, <i>Roman by Polanski</i>, sometimes known as <i>Roman</i>.</li>
</ul>
